ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It's should be a mandatory course for students in economics, finance, etc.
it is compulsory for marketing students.

The course is an excellent doctoral-level introduction to probability theory and econometrics. It's also extremely challenging. I would recommend the course to all students in economics, statistics, and related disciplines, but probably not to anyone outside.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: After taking this course, I strengthen my knowledge in econometrics which expand my view in economics.
It is useful to understand more advanced models and methods that i am going to use in my dissertation.
The most valuable addition has been a delicate balance between rigor and comprehensibility in the way in which measure theory, one of the most intricate subdisciplines of mathematics, was taught.
Essential for doctoral students in economics and statistics.
